	<h4><a href=""><img src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar.php?gravatar_id=0804f892615735bd76e32db4429d4011&amp;size=100&amp;default=http%3A%2F%2Fcloud.24ways.org%2Fimg%2Fgravatar.png" class="gravatar" alt="" height="100" width="100" /> Jaye <small></small></a></h4>
		<p>For anyone else battling Outlook 2007 where images are misaligned or splitting apart, you can try this fix. We have <span class="caps">HTML</span> emails with lots of images and some of them act as links. If there is an &lt;align&gt; tag on the image that is wrapped in an &lt;a&gt;  tag, then Outlook 2007 seems to add one pixel padding to the top and bottom of the image. Once we had removed &lt;align=&#8220;left&#8221;&gt; from the image tag, it tightened up nicely. Not sure why this happens, but mine is not to question, just fix it.</p>

	<p><span class="caps">BTW</span> &#8212; Awesome article, thanks!</p>


